Assignment 1:
0) install angular cli
 $ npm install -g @angular/cli
 setup nodemon
 $ npm install -g nodemon
1) git clone https://github.com/jannunzi/angular-four-MEAN-seed
2) mv angular-four-MEAN-seed webdev
3) cd webdev
4) npm install
5) mongod
6) run the front end using angular 4, this will start a local embedded server that will serve the Angular front end. You can stop the front end with Ctrl+c twice
   $ npm start
7) in a separate terminal, run the backend using Node.js. you can stop the backend with Ctrl+C
   $ nodemon server.js


